text: Scarab is a professional fraternity in the field of Architecture. It was founded on February 25, 1909 at University of Illinois at Urbana–ChampaignProfessional Fraternities by Professional Interfraternity Conference - 1950 The Publication was "The Hieratic", ==Chapter list== Scarab Chapter list and temple name *1909 University of Illinois at Urbana–Champaign (Karnak) *1914 Washington University in St. Louis (Ipsamboul) *1915 Illinois Institute of Technology (Edfou) *1916 Pennsylvania State University (Thebes) *1920 Carnegie Institute of Technology (Philae) *1921 Massachusetts Institute of Technology (Luxor) *1921 University of Kansas (Abydos) *1926 George Washington University (Ammon) *1926 University of Minnesota (Khons) *1927 University of Southern California (Isis) *1928 University of Virginia (Hathor) *1929 University of Cincinnati (Osiris) *1932 Washington State University (Horus) *1932 Auburn University (Khufu) *1954 California State Polytechnic University, Pomona *1955 Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute ==References== Category:1909 establishments in Illinois Category:Student organizations established in 1909 Category:Professional fraternities and sororities in the United States Category:Professional Fraternity Association
